{
  "text": "Cross-presentation refers to the ability of limited subsets of APCs, primarily Batf3-dependent DCs (CD8a DCs show a reduced capacity to cross-present MHC-Irestricted antigens to diabetogenic CD8 1 T cells [CITATION_1] . This defect may limit the presentation of certain islet cell-derived epitopes to induce tolerance. Cross-presentation of certain b-cell antigens by B cells also exacerbates T1D [CITATION_2] . In humans, cross-presentation may be affected by polymorphism in the RAC2 and MAP3K14 genes (Supplementary Table 2 ).",
  "correct_citation": {
